KPat — Windows build notice
===========================

This is an UNOFFICIAL Windows build of KPat (KDE Patience) produced from
the fork at https://github.com/panibor/kpat. KPat is part of the KDE
Gear / KDE Release Service; the original, official upstream repository
lives at https://invent.kde.org/games/kpat and is maintained by the KDE
community. This fork is not endorsed by KDE.

Modifications in this fork (GPL v2 §2(a))
-----------------------------------------

Date of modification: 2026-05-18

Changes versus upstream:

  .github/workflows/windows.yml   GitHub Actions workflow that builds KPat
                                  for Windows using KDE Craft.
  .github/dependabot.yml          Keeps the workflow's pinned action
                                  versions current.
  NOTICE.windows                  This file.
  README.windows.md               Build / install documentation for the
                                  Windows binaries.
  src/main.cpp                    Windows-only palette fix (~20 lines,
                                  guarded by #ifdef Q_OS_WIN). Qt 6.7+'s
                                  default windows11 widget style returns
                                  identical colours for QPalette::Highlight
                                  and QPalette::HighlightedText on some
                                  Windows 11 versions, hiding the labels of
                                  selected items in KConfigDialog sidebars.
                                  The patch detects a low-contrast collision
                                  and forces a readable HighlightedText
                                  colour while leaving every other palette
                                  role untouched, so the native Windows 11
                                  look (icons, frames, accent colour) is
                                  preserved. No KPat behaviour outside
                                  selection-text rendering is affected, and
                                  the fix is a no-op on Linux/macOS.

No file under autotests/, icons/, themes/, sounds/, doc/, po/, mimetypes/,
previews/, libkcardgame/, patsolve/, CMakeLists.txt, CMakePresets.json, or
any other source/build file of KPat itself has been modified beyond the
Windows-specific palette fix noted above. The shipped binary is otherwise
built from the unmodified KPat source as tagged on this fork's branch.

Installer metadata
------------------

To avoid misrepresenting the origin of this binary, the GitHub Actions
workflow patches the upstream KDE Craft blueprint for KPat at build time
so the NSIS installer (and therefore the Windows "Installed apps" list)
ships these strings:

  Publisher / Company    panibor (Unofficial KPat for Windows)
  Version                <upstream RELEASE_SERVICE_VERSION>-win-<sha>
  Website / Help link    https://github.com/panibor/kpat

Upstream KDE Craft's defaults are "KDE e.V." for the publisher and the
literal git ref ("HEAD" for a branch-tip build) for the version. Those
defaults are accurate for KDE's own binary factory but would falsely
attribute this build to KDE e.V. and obscure which fork revision was
shipped. The override only changes installer metadata strings; it does
not modify KPat source, the KDE Craft repository, or the upstream
craft-blueprints-kde repository (the patch is applied to the fetched
copy inside the build environment and is discarded with that environment
when the CI job finishes). KDE and the KDE community are not endorsing,
publishing, or distributing this build.

